<section id="consumables">
	<h2>Consumables</h2>

	<h3>Flasks</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Phial of Tepid Versatility</strong> - Good balance between defensive and offensive boosts. A reliable choice for general dungeon/raid tanking.</li>
		<li><strong>Phial of Static Empowerment</strong> - For situations where you don't need to move much. Great when you’re confident on bosses with little movement requirements.</li>
		<li><strong>Phial of Elemental Chaos</strong> - Random effects, can provide large Haste buffs but less predictable. Risky but high reward in DPS heavy situations.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Food</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Feast Buffs</strong> - Take whatever your raid uses for Feasts; these usually give large amounts of Strength or Haste.</li>
		<li><strong>Individual Food</strong> - Choose Haste food or Mastery food if eating solo. Examples: Timely Demise (Haste) or Grand Banquet of the Kalu'ak for Strength.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Potions</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Elemental Potion of Power</strong> - Provides a large Strength buff. Used pre-pull or during burst phases to maximize Avenging Wrath DPS and Shield of the Righteous spam.</li>
		<li><strong>Refreshing Healing Potion</strong> - Instant heal potion. Always keep a few on you for emergencies when Word of Glory and Lay on Hands are not available.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Weapon Oils</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Buzzing Rune</strong> - Boosts Haste. Best choice for smooth rotation and Shield of the Righteous uptime.</li>
		<li><strong>Howling Rune</strong> - Boosts Critical Strike. Not generally preferred over Buzzing Rune unless you are already capped on Haste.</li>
		<li><strong>Chirping Rune</strong> - Boosts Versatility. Good fallback for more durability at the cost of less throughput.</li>
	</ul>

